		<h2>Overview</h2>
		<p>There are 4 different types of Spanish work contracts, on this page we'll give an overview of each one and provide you a download link with the Spanish version and a translated English version. Keep this in mind when you sign a contract at your future job since the work contract <strong>must be in Spanish for it to be valid</strong> but having an English version for reference can help you understand some of your rights and what you're signing.</p>
		<br>
		<h5>Contrato Indefinido - Indefinite Contract</h5>
		<p>Indefinite contracts are contracts that are concluded without establishing time limits in terms of the duration of the contract. They are therefore adequate to offer stability, commitment and good working conditions.</p>
